Value Fabric - 4-Layer Build Plan (Detailed Specifications)
Build the Value Fabric enterprise AI platform incrementally through 4 layers using Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Neo4j, and LangGraph. Each layer is a standalone microservice with Docker Compose orchestration.

Global Rules Reference
Apply these across all layers:

Python 3.11+ with async/await, strict type hints (mypy)
Google-style docstrings, Black formatting, Ruff linting (zero warnings)
Absolute imports only: stdlib → third-party → local
Conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, test:)
Test coverage: Layer 2 requires 85% minimum
All data requires provenance (URL + timestamp)
Confidence scores (0.0-1.0) on all LLM outputs
No hardcoded secrets (environment variables only)
Prometheus metrics, structured JSON logging, OpenTelemetry traces
API design: RESTful, /v1/ prefix, standardized error format
See full Global Rules document for: Data Governance, Security, Observability, Testing, Deployment, AI/LLM Governance, Incident Response

Build Order
Phase 1: Layer 2 → Phase 2: Layer 3 → Phase 3: Layer 4 → Phase 4: Layer 1

Rationale: Start with Layer 2 because it defines the core ontology (Capability, UseCase, Persona, ValueDriver) used by all other layers. It can be tested with sample Markdown data without requiring full ingestion infrastructure.

Layer 1: Intelligent Data Ingestion Service
Status: Phase 4 (after Layer 3) Technology Stack: Python 3.11+, Playwright (async), Celery + Redis, PostgreSQL, MinIO/S3

Core Components:

Scheduler Service: Determines what to crawl, manages priorities
Crawler Workers: Headless browser instances (Playwright) executing extraction
Post-Processor: Cleans, deduplicates, normalizes raw content to Markdown
Data Sources:

Priority 1: Corporate websites, SEC EDGAR filings (10-K, 10-Q), earnings call transcripts
Priority 2: Competitor documentation, industry analyst reports, patent filings
Priority 3: LinkedIn company pages, news mentions via NewsAPI
Compliance (NON-NEGOTIABLE):

robots.txt parser with 24-hour cache, respect Crawl-delay, never crawl Disallow paths
Rate limiting: Global 1000 req/min, per-domain 1 req/sec with 20% jitter
PII detection with Microsoft Presidio: redact SSN, credit cards, phone, email; block pages with >3 PII entities
Audit log: URL, timestamp, IP, bytes downloaded, outcome (7-year retention)
API Endpoints:

POST /crawl/website → {job_id, estimated_pages}
GET /crawl/status/{job_id} → {status, pages_crawled, pages_total}
POST /crawl/sec-filings → Fetch EDGAR filings by ticker
GET /content/{content_id} → Markdown + metadata
DELETE /content/{content_id} → Soft delete with 30-day retention
Deliverables: Docker Compose, K8s manifests, Terraform for AWS, pytest suite, Locust load tests, Prometheus metrics, OpenAPI spec, runbook

Acceptance Criteria: 1000+ pages/day, zero robots.txt violations, >95% PII detection accuracy, 4+/5 Markdown readability, 99.5% API uptime

Layer 2: Ontology-Guided Extraction Pipeline [BUILD FIRST - Phase 1]
Technology Stack: Python 3.11+, Pydantic v2, OpenAI/Anthropic (function calling), LangChain, Celery + Redis, rdflib

Core Ontology (Pydantic v2 Models)
python
class Capability(BaseModel):
    id: str = Field(default_factory=lambda: str(uuid4()))
    name: str  # e.g., "Real-Time Data Ingestion"
    description: str
    technical_features: List[str]
    api_endpoints: List[str] = []
    integrations: List[str] = []
    apqc_mapping: Optional[str]  # APQC PCF code
    source_refs: List[str]  # URLs where mentioned
 
class UseCase(BaseModel):
    id: str
    name: str  # e.g., "Touchless Accounts Payable"
    description: str
    industry_context: List[str]  # ["Finance", "Manufacturing"]
    required_capabilities: List[str]  # Capability IDs
    workflow_steps: List[str]
    kpis: List[str]
 
class Persona(BaseModel):
    id: str
    role_type: Literal["economic_buyer", "operational_user", "stakeholder"]
    title: str  # e.g., "Chief Financial Officer"
    department: str
    pain_points: List[str]
    success_metrics: List[str]
    influenced_by: List[str] = []  # Other persona IDs
 
class ValueDriver(BaseModel):
    id: str
    category: Literal["revenue", "cost", "risk", "capital"]
    name: str  # e.g., "Operational Cost Reduction"
    description: str
    metrics: List[str]
    formula_string: Optional[str]  # e.g., "({hours_saved} * {hourly_rate}) - {implementation_cost}"
    unit: str  # e.g., "USD", "percentage"
    time_to_value: Optional[str]  # e.g., "3-6 months"
Relationship Types:

enables: Capability → UseCase
requires: UseCase → Capability
benefits: UseCase → Persona
drives: Persona → ValueDriver
contributes_to: Capability → ValueDriver
depends_on: Capability → Capability
alternative_to: Capability → Capability
python
class Relationship(BaseModel):
    source_id: str
    predicate: Literal["enables", "requires", "benefits", "drives", "contributes_to", "depends_on", "alternative_to"]
    target_id: str
    confidence: float = Field(ge=0.0, le=1.0)
    evidence_text: str  # Quote from source
    source_url: str
Extraction Pipeline (6 Stages)
Chunking & Preprocessing
Semantic chunking: LangChain RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter
Chunk size: 2000 tokens, overlap: 200 tokens
Preserve paragraph boundaries, tag with metadata
Entity Extraction (LLM Call 1)
Model: GPT-4o or Claude 3.5 Sonnet
Temperature: 0.0 (deterministic)
Function calling with strict schema
Confidence threshold: 0.8
Relationship Extraction (LLM Call 2)
Input: Extracted entities
Only create relationships with explicit evidence
Confidence threshold: 0.75
Semantic Alignment & Deduplication
Embeddings: text-embedding-3-large
Similarity threshold: 0.85 for merging
Keep canonical entity (most source refs)
Entailment validation for subclasses
Validation & Normalization
Pydantic schema validation
Check required fields, valid enum values
Resolve all ID references (no dangling)
Normalize: lowercase for matching, preserve original in display_name
RDF/OWL Serialization
Turtle format with prefixes: vf:, prov:
OWL axioms for transitive properties
PROV-O provenance metadata
Industry Standard Integration:

APQC PCF v7.4 mapping: embedding index, similarity >0.8
Optional: BIAN Service Landscape v11.0, FIBO ontology for financial services
API Endpoints:

POST /extract → {extraction_job_id, status}
